Greetings Padawan Quantum,

Thank you for the comment and taking the time to read my blog. I wish you luck on your journey of discovery. Those of us who are travelers have to make that choice to stop climbing the ladder that is quickly losing its functioning and enjoy the journey, learn from the mistakes, have fun and live our lives to the fullest – whatever this means for us.

You may need to consider why your mother is displacing the negative energy and creating dramatic episodes. If it is just grief, it may not stop for a long time.

As far as the United States, try to observe with objective analysis. Is it a truly better place for a Tai Chi practitioner? Many go there with expectations that Tai Chi teachers and schools will be great, but I find that in my teaching experience many students have been past practicing it or very organized, optimistic people with an eye of collecting power through whatever means to become bosses of a club, a company or the Tai Chi Yin or Yang. A traveling Tai Chi practitioner knows the good and bad in one country or another. I recommend being open minded to things in any place you
